rComments: I highly recommend staying away from this professor. Her course material is not difficult, however her grading is unfair due to the lack of instructions and clarity. She seems to deduct marks if phrases are not specifically how she would word them and is not understanding when asking for revisions. She was also late to multiple lectures.

While this class was an easy A for me, the prof made it so hard to keep motivated and focused. She makes us read hundreds of pages per week and never does anything with the information in them. She is confused about her own material and makes a lot of mistakes in her slides. Participation matters, but she wont give students time to talk.

most bad rates frm 1st yrs who didnt follow instructions/ask for help. lots of readings at the start but prof was receptive to feedback & cut them back. gave us extensions on 2 tasks. instructions somewhat unclear (but not rlly cuz it's anthro so u can bs easily). content is interesting and good lecturer. exam was easy and had 3 days to do it
